dsRpStEsfErrors.name: dsRpStEsfErrors
dsRpStEsfErrors.description: The total number of Error Free Seconds since the counters have last been cleared.

dsRpStCrcErrors.name: dsRpStCrcErrors
dsRpStCrcErrors.description: The total number of CRC errors since the counters have last been cleared.

dsRpStOofErrors.name: dsRpStOofErrors

dsRpStYellowEvents.name: dsRpStYellowEvents

dsPlBreak.name: dsPlBreak
dsPlBreak.description: This object determines if the user interface uses page breaks or 'more' prompts when displaying information which is longer than the defined page length (e.g., output from UNLR or SCV). A page length of 0 will disable both page breaks and 'more' prompts. VALUE DESCRIPTION rpPlLineFeed(1) Use linefeeds for page breaks rpPlMorePrompt(2) Use 'more' prompts for page breaks

dsPlLen.name: dsPlLen
dsPlLen.description: The length of a 'page' of information. When the set number of lines have been displayed, a 'more' prompt or linefeed will be inserted (defined by dsPlBreak). A page length of 0 causes output to scroll continuously without page breaks or 'more' prompts.

dsRpAhrEntry.name: dsRpAhrEntry
dsRpAhrEntry.description: An entry in the Alarm History Table.

dsRpAhrIndex.name: dsRpAhrIndex
dsRpAhrIndex.description: The Alarm History Table index. Index 1 is the most recent alarm.

dsRpAhrStr.name: dsRpAhrStr
dsRpAhrStr.description: The alarm message in USER format.

dsRpShrTable.name: dsRpShrTable
dsRpShrTable.description: This is the Security History Report table. It contains entries for events which are considered important from a security standpoint. Examples of such events are 1) incorrect Telnet password entered and 2) source IP address not on IP Screen List. The entries are placed in chronological order, with most recent event first.

dsRpShrEntry.name: dsRpShrEntry
dsRpShrEntry.description: An entry in the Security History Report table.

dsRpShrIndex.name: dsRpShrIndex
dsRpShrIndex.description: The Security History Report table index. Events are in chronological order. This number ranges between 1 and the value of dsRpShrNumber. Index 1 is the most recent event.

dsRpShrDateTime.name: dsRpShrDateTime
dsRpShrDateTime.description: Display string showing date & time that the security related event occurred.

dsRpShrEventType.name: dsRpShrEventType
dsRpShrEventType.description: Shows what type of security related event occurred. VALUE DESCRIPTION rpShrTelnetPassword (1) - Incorrect Telnet password entered rpShrSrcIpAddressScreen (2) - Source IP address not on IP Screen List rpShrReadCommString (3) - Incorrect SNMP Read Community String rpShrWriteCommString (4) - Incorrect SNMP Write Community String

dsRpShrComments.name: dsRpShrComments
dsRpShrComments.description: Display string showing additional information specific to the type of event. For example, for events of type rpShrTelnetPassword, the IP address of the remote host is given.

dsRpSes.name: dsRpSes

dsRpFrTmCnt2Hrs.name: dsRpFrTmCnt2Hrs

dsRpFrTmCntDays.name: dsRpFrTmCntDays
dsRpFrTmCntDays.description: The number of completed days in the Day Table.

dsRpFrPre15MEntry.name: dsRpFrPre15MEntry
dsRpFrPre15MEntry.description: An entry in the FRIB Previous 15 Min Table.

dsRpFrPre15MDir.name: dsRpFrPre15MDir
dsRpFrPre15MDir.description: The direction index to the FRIB Previous 15 Min Table. VALUE DESCRIPTION 1 Transmit 2 Receive

dsRpFrTotalTable.name: dsRpFrTotalTable
dsRpFrTotalTable.description: The FRIB Total Table. This table contains performance information for the past 24-hours for Frame Relay data being passed throught the NI Interface. This is a rolling count. When the current 2-hour interval is up, the last entry in the interval table will be removed and the completed 2-hour interval added. At this point the Total Table will be re-calculated.

dsRpFrTotalEntry.description: An entry in the FRIB Total Table.

dsRpFrDayTable.name: dsRpFrDayTable
dsRpFrDayTable.description: After the unit has been powered up for 24 hours, the values from the FRIB Total Table are moved into the first slot in the FRIB Day Table. There are seven entries in the FRIB Day Table, so an entire week's history is maintained. The previous day is always in slot 1.

dsRpFrDayFpLost.name: dsRpFrDayFpLost

dsRpFrDayFpSent.name: dsRpFrDayFpSent

dsRpFrUrEIRExceededOctets.description: The number of octets that exceeded the EIR threshold.

dsRpDdsEntry.description: This is an entry in the DDS Table.

dsRpDdsIfIndex.description: The index into the table. This is mib-II's ifIndex.

dsLmLoopback.name: dsLmLoopback
dsLmLoopback.description: This is the type of loopback that is currently active. The values have the following meanings: VALUE DESCRIPTION lmLbkNone(1) No loopback is set lmLbkLine(2) Line loopback is set lmLbkPayload(3) Payload loopback is set lmLbkLocal(4) Local loopback is set lmLbkTiTest(5) TI looback is set lmLbkDp1(6) Data port 1 loopback is set lmLbkDp2(7) Data port 2 loopback is set lmLbkDt1(8) Data terminal loopback on data port 1 is set lmLbkDt2(9) Data terminal loopback on data port 2 is set lmLbkCsu(10) CSU Loopback (DDS) lmLbkDsu(11) DSU Loopback (DDS) lmLbkDpdt(12) Data-Port/Data-Terminal LB

dsLmSelfTestState.name: dsLmSelfTestState
dsLmSelfTestState.description: This object will start a self test operation when set to lmSelfTestStart(2). At the completion of the test, it will return to its normal state of lmSelfTestIdle(1).

dsLmSelfTestResults.name: dsLmSelfTestResults
dsLmSelfTestResults.description: The results of the last self test operation.

dsRmLbkCode.name: dsRmLbkCode
dsRmLbkCode.description: The type of remote loopback that is currently set. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION rmRNone(1) No loopback is set rmRst1(2) A remote loopback reset code is currenlty being sent rmRLine(3) A remote Line loopback is set rmRPayload(4) A remote Payload loopback is set rmRDp1(5) A remote Data Port 1 loopback is set rmRDp2(6) A remote Data Port 2 loopback is set

dsRmTestCode.name: dsRmTestCode
dsRmTestCode.description: The type of remote test code that is currently being sent. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION rmTestNone(1) No test code is being sent rmTestQrs(2) QRS is being sent rmTest324(3) 3-in-24 is being sent rmTestOnes(4) All ones is being sent rmTestZeros(5) All zeros is being sent rmTest511Dp1(6) 511 is being sent out data port 1 rmTest511Dp2(7) 511 is being sent out data port 2 rmTest2047Dp1(8) 2047 is being sent out data port 1 rmTest2047Dp2(9) 2047 is being sent out data port 2 rmTest2toThe23(10) 2 to the 23 is being sent rmTest2toThe15(11) 2 to the 15 is being sent

dsRmBertState.name: dsRmBertState
dsRmBertState.description: The current BERT state. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION rmBertIdle(1) No BERT test is active rmBertOtherStart(2) BERT was started from the control port, front panel, or Telnet rmBertSearching(3) BERT was started from the agent and has not yet detected the code rmBertFound(4) BERT was started from the agent and has detected the code

dsRmBertCode.name: dsRmBertCode
dsRmBertCode.description: This object controls the activation of BERT tests. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION rmBertNone(1) No BERT test is active rmBertQrs(2) BERT for QRS rmBert324(3) BERT for 3-in-24 rmBertOnes(4) BERT for all ones rmBertZeros(5) BERT for all zeros rmBert511Dp1(6) BERT for 511 on data port 1 rmBert511Dp2(7) BERT for 511 on data port 2 rmBert2047Dp1(8) BERT for 2047 on data port 1 rmBert2047Dp2(9) BERT for 2047 on data port 2 rmTest2toThe23(10) BERT for 2 to the 23 rmTest2toThe15(11) BERT for 2 to the 15

dsRmBertTestSecs.name: dsRmBertTestSecs
dsRmBertTestSecs.description: The number of seconds the requested test code has been detected since the start of the BERT.

dsRmBertBitErrors.name: dsRmBertBitErrors
dsRmBertBitErrors.description: The number of bit errors detected since the start of the BERT.

dsRmBertErrdSecs.name: dsRmBertErrdSecs
dsRmBertErrdSecs.description: The number of errored seconds detected since the start of the BERT.

dsRmBertTotalErrors.name: dsRmBertTotalErrors
dsRmBertTotalErrors.description: The number of total errors detected since the start of the BERT.

dsRmBertReSync.name: dsRmBertReSync
dsRmBertReSync.description: The number of times BERT has lost and re-aquired the pattern.

dsRmFpingAction.name: dsRmFpingAction
dsRmFpingAction.description: The control actions for the FPING test. Possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION rmFpingStart(1) Start sending FPINGs rmFpingStop(2) Stop sending FPINGs

dsRmFpingState.name: dsRmFpingState
dsRmFpingState.description: The current state of the FPING tester. Possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION rmFpingIdle(1) No FPINGs are being generated rmFpingOtherStart(2) FPINGs are being generated. The test was started via one of the other management interfaces. rmFpingRunning(3) FPINGs are being generated. The test was started via SNMP.

dsRmFpingVc.name: dsRmFpingVc
dsRmFpingVc.description: The VC that FPINGs will be sent on. VC values range from (0..1023) if the Frame Relay address length is 2 octets and (0..8388607) if the address length is 4 octets. Default is 500.

dsRmFpingFreq.name: dsRmFpingFreq
dsRmFpingFreq.description: The frequency (in seconds) that FPING packets will be transmitted. The range is (5..255). Default is 5.

dsRmFpingLen.name: dsRmFpingLen
dsRmFpingLen.description: The length (in octets) of the payload portion of the FPING packets. The range is (0..1400). Default is 0.

dsRmFpingCur.name: dsRmFpingCur
dsRmFpingCur.description: The roundtrip time (in msec) of the last FPING sent.

dsRmFpingMin.name: dsRmFpingMin
dsRmFpingMin.description: The minimum roundtrip time (in msec) of all FPINGs sent during this test.

dsRmFpingMax.name: dsRmFpingMax
dsRmFpingMax.description: The maximum roundtrip time (in msec) of all FPINGs sent during this test.

dsRmFpingAvg.name: dsRmFpingAvg
dsRmFpingAvg.description: The average roundtrip time (in msec) of all FPINGs sent during this test.

dsRmFpingLost.name: dsRmFpingLost
dsRmFpingLost.description: The number of FPING packets lost during this test.

dsRmFpingTotal.name: dsRmFpingTotal
dsRmFpingTotal.description: The total number of FPING packets transmitted during this test.

dsRmFpingRmtVc.name: dsRmFpingRmtVc
dsRmFpingRmtVc.description: The VC used at the remote end of the circuit.

dsRmFpingRmtIp.name: dsRmFpingRmtIp
dsRmFpingRmtIp.description: The IP address of the unit responding to FPINGs.

dsRmInsertBitError.name: dsRmInsertBitError
dsRmInsertBitError.description: Possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION insertBitError(1) Start sending FPINGs noInsertBitError(2) Stop sending FPINGs

dsAcAlmMsg.name: dsAcAlmMsg
dsAcAlmMsg.description: This object controls the displaying/sending of alarm messages. Alarm messages will be sent in the format determined by dsAcAlmFormat if dsAcAlmMsg is set to acAlmMsgEnable(1). Alarm messages will not be sent if this object is set to acAlmMsgDisable(2).

dsAcYelAlm.name: dsAcYelAlm
dsAcYelAlm.description: This object determines if incoming Yellow Alarm will cause an alarm message to be sent. Setting this object to acYelAlmEnable(1) causes an alarm to be sent when Yellow Alarm is received on the Network or Terminal Interface. Setting this object to acYelAlmDisable(2) will not send an alarm when Yellow Alarm is received.

dsAcDeact.name: dsAcDeact
dsAcDeact.description: This object controls the number of seconds an alarm condition must remain clear before the unit declares it cleared. The range is from 0 to 15 seconds.

dsAcEst.name: dsAcEst
dsAcEst.description: This object determines the threshold of errored seconds that triggers an Excessive Error Rate (EER) alarm. Setting this object to zero disables errored seconds causing an EER alarm.

dsAcUst.name: dsAcUst
dsAcUst.description: This object determines the threshold of uavailable seconds that triggers an Excessive Error Rate (EER) alarm. Setting this object to zero disables unavailable seconds causing an EER alarm.

dsAcSt.name: dsAcSt
dsAcSt.description: This object determines the window used to calculate whether an Excessive Error Rate (EER) alarm should be generated from errored seconds or unavailable seconds. Setting this object to acSt15(1) establishes a 15-minute sliding window. Setting this object to acSt60(2) establishes a 60-minute sliding window.

dsAcBerAlm.name: dsAcBerAlm
dsAcBerAlm.description: This object controls the sending of a Bit Error Rate (BER) alarm. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION acBerAlmEnable(1) Enable sending BER alarms acBerAlmDisable(2) Disable sending BER alarms

dsAcRfaAlm.name: dsAcRfaAlm
dsAcRfaAlm.description: This object controls the sending of a Remote Frame Alarm (RFA). The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION acRfaAlmEnable(1) Enable sending RFA alarms acRfaAlmDisable(2) Disable sending RFA alarms

dsAcAisAlm.name: dsAcAisAlm
dsAcAisAlm.description: This object controls the sending of Alarm Indication Signal (AIS) alarms. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION acAisAlmEnable(1) Enable sending AIS alarms acAisAlmDisable(2) Disable sending AIS alarms

dsAcOnPowerTransition.name: dsAcOnPowerTransition
dsAcOnPowerTransition.description: A/B On Power Transition on DataSMART 558 and MPATH 538

dsAcOffPowerTransition.name: dsAcOffPowerTransition
dsAcOffPowerTransition.description: A/B Off Power Transition on DataSMART 558 and MPATH 538

dsCcEcho.name: dsCcEcho
dsCcEcho.description: This object controls character echo on the control port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ccEchoEnable(1) Enable control port echo ccEchoDisable(2) Disable control port echo

dsCcControlPort.name: dsCcControlPort
dsCcControlPort.description: This object determines whether the control port is the DCE or DTE port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ccDce(1) The control port is the DCE port ccDte(2) The control port is the DTE port

dsCcBaud.name: dsCcBaud
dsCcBaud.description: The baud rate of the control port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION cc2400(1) 2400 baud cc9600(2) 9600 baud cc19200(3) 19200 baud cc38400(4) 38400 baud

dsCcParity.name: dsCcParity
dsCcParity.description: The parity of the control port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ccNone(1) No parity ccEven(2) Even parity ccOdd(3) Odd parity

dsCcDataBits.name: dsCcDataBits
dsCcDataBits.description: The number of data bits for the control port. The possible values are: VALUES DESCRIPTION cc7Bit(1) 7 data bits cc8Bit(2) 8 data bits

dsCcStopBits.name: dsCcStopBits
dsCcStopBits.description: The number of stop bits for the control port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION cc1Bit(1) 1 stop bit cc2Bit(2) 2 stop bits

dsCcDceIn.name: dsCcDceIn
dsCcDceIn.description: The input status of the DCE signals RTS and DTR. The possible valuesa re: VALUE DESCRIPTION ccBothOff(1) RTS off, DTR off ccRtsOnDtrOff(2) RTS on, DTR off ccRtsOffDtrOn(3) RTS off, DTR on ccBothOn(4) RTS on, DTR on

dsCcDteIn.name: dsCcDteIn
dsCcDteIn.description: The input status of the DTE signals CTS and DCD. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ccBothOff(1) CTS off, DCD off ccCtsOnDcdOff(2) CTS on, DCD off ccCTSoffDCDon(3) CTS off, DCD on ccBothOn(4) CTS on, DCD on

dsDcTable.name: dsDcTable
dsDcTable.description: The Data Port Configuration Table. This table contains information on the configuration of each of the unit's data ports.

dsDcEntry.name: dsDcEntry
dsDcEntry.description: An entry in the Data Port Configuration Table.

dsDcIndex.name: dsDcIndex
dsDcIndex.description: The index to the Data Port Configuration Table. The possible values are 1 through 2.

dsDcDataInvert.name: dsDcDataInvert
dsDcDataInvert.description: The data inversion of the data port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION dcDataInvertEnable(1) Invert the data port signal dcDataInvertDisable(2) Don't invert the data port signal

dsDcInterface.name: dsDcInterface
dsDcInterface.description: The type of electrical interface the data port is using. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION dcV35Interface(1) V.35 dcEia530Interface(2) EIA-530 dcV35DSInterface (3) V.35 DataSMART Compatible

dsDcClockSource.name: dsDcClockSource
dsDcClockSource.description: The clock source for the data port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION dcInternalClock(1) Use the internal clock dcExternalClock(2) Use the external clock

dsDcXmtClkInvert.name: dsDcXmtClkInvert
dsDcXmtClkInvert.description: The inversion status of the transmit clock signal for the data port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION dcXClkInvertEnable(1) Invert the transmit clock signal dcXClkInvertDisable(2) Don't invert the transmit clock signal

dsDcRcvClkInvert.name: dsDcRcvClkInvert
dsDcRcvClkInvert.description: The inversion status of the received clock signal for the data port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION dcRClkInvertEnable(1) Invert the received clock signal dcRClkInvertDisable(2) Don't invert the received clock signal

dsDcIdleChar.name: dsDcIdleChar
dsDcIdleChar.description: The idle character to use for the data port. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION dc7eIdleChar(1) The idle character is hex 7E dc7fIdleChar(1) The idle character is hex 7F dcffIdleChar(3) The idle character is hex FF

dsDcLOSInput.name: dsDcLOSInput
dsDcLOSInput.description: The combination of RTS and DTR that will cause a data port Loss of Signal alarm. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION dcLosNone(1) Data port LOS is disabled dcLosRts(2) LOS is declared when RTS is lost dcLosDtr(3) LOS is declared when DTR is lost dcLosBoth(4) LOS is declared when both RTS and DTR are lost.

dsFcLoadXcute.name: dsFcLoadXcute
dsFcLoadXcute.description: The Fractional Table that is active. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION fcLoadXcuteIdle(1) The normal state fcLoadXcuteStartA(2) Load and execute table A fcLoadXcuteStartB(3) Load and execute table B

dsFcTable.name: dsFcTable
dsFcTable.description: This is the DS1/E1 Fractional Table. This table consists of configuration information about DS1/E1 fractional services.

dsFcEntry.name: dsFcEntry
dsFcEntry.description: This is an entry in the Fractional Table.

dsFcTableIndex.name: dsFcTableIndex
dsFcTableIndex.description: This is the index into the Fractional Table. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION 1 Stored configuration A 2 Stored configuration B 3 Currently executing fractional table

dsFcChanIndex.name: dsFcChanIndex
dsFcChanIndex.description: This is the index of the fractional channel. DS1 has 24 channels and E1 has 32.

dsFcChanMap.name: dsFcChanMap
dsFcChanMap.description: The destination and data rate of the channel. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION fcChanIdle(1) The channel is idle fcChanTiData(2) The channel carries data and is mapped to a TI channel fcChanTiVoice(3) The channel carries voice and is mapped to a TI channel fcChan56Dp1(4) The cahnnel is set for 56K and is mapped to data port 1 fcChan64Dp1(5) The channel is set for 64K and is mapped to data port 1 fcChan56Dp2(6) The channel is set for 56K and is mapped to data port 2 fcChan64Dp2(7) The channel is set for 64K and is mapped to data port 2 fcChanDLNK(8) The channel is idle and set for data link communications fcChanDPDL(9) The channel is active and also set for data link communications fCchanUanv(10) The channel is unavailable

dsFcMap16.name: dsFcMap16
dsFcMap16.description: This object determines if channel 16 is available for user payload data. This is only possible if the unit is configured for Common Channel Signalling. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION fcMap16Used(1) Channel 16 cannot be used for user payload data fcMap16Unused(2) Channel 16 is available for user payload data

dsFmcFrameType.name: dsFmcFrameType
dsFmcFrameType.description: The frame type for packets being transmitted and received for IP connectivity. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION fmcFrNlpid(1) Frame Relay NLPID encapsulation fmcFrEther(2) Frame Relay Ethertype encapsulation fmcAtmNlpid(3) ATM DXI NLPID encapsulation fmcAtmLlcSnap(4) ATM DXI LLC/SNAP encapsulation fmcAtmVcMux(5) ATM DXI VC-based multiplexing

dsFmcAddrOctets.name: dsFmcAddrOctets
dsFmcAddrOctets.description: The length in octets of the Frame Relay address. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION fmc2Octets(1) The address is 2 octets long fmc4Octets(1) The address is 4 octets long

dsFmcFcsBits.name: dsFmcFcsBits
dsFmcFcsBits.description: The length in bits of the Frame Relay FCS. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION fmc16Bits(1) The FCS field is 16 bits long fmc32Bits(2) The FCS field is 32 bits long

dsFmcUpperBW.name: dsFmcUpperBW
dsFmcUpperBW.description: The percent of bandwidth utilization threshold. If the threshold is exceeded, an event will be recorded in the performance data and a trap (if configured) will be sent. Valid values are 5-95 in increments of 5.

dsFmcFpingOper.name: dsFmcFpingOper
dsFmcFpingOper.description: The enabling and disabling of FPING operation. Valid values are Enable and Disable.

dsFmcFpingGen.name: dsFmcFpingGen
dsFmcFpingGen.description: The number of distinct VC to be received on the NI before FPINGs are automatically sent out.

dsFmcFpingThres.name: dsFmcFpingThres
dsFmcFpingThres.description: The maximum roundtrip time of a FPING packet in milliseconds. If the threshold is exceeded, an event will be recorded in the performance data and a trap (if configured) will be sent. Valid values are 20-2000 in increments of 10.

dsFmcFpingRst.name: dsFmcFpingRst
dsFmcFpingRst.description: Reset the specified VC to an initial state where FPING connectivity is check for. Valid values are 0-1023 for a 2 octet address field and 0-8388607 for a 4 octet address field.

dsFmcAddVc.name: dsFmcAddVc
dsFmcAddVc.description: Add a VC to the list of monitored VCs

dsFmcDelVc.name: dsFmcDelVc
dsFmcDelVc.description: Del a VC from the list of monitored VCs. Any statistics related to this VC will be moved to the 'other' category.

dsFmcSetNiRcvUpperBwThresh.name: dsFmcSetNiRcvUpperBwThresh
dsFmcSetNiRcvUpperBwThresh.description: The total traffic through the unit has exceeded the configured threshold for NI Receive.

dsFmcClrNiRcvUpperBwThresh.name: dsFmcClrNiRcvUpperBwThresh
dsFmcClrNiRcvUpperBwThresh.description: The total traffic through the unit has crossed back under 20 percent below the configured threshold after exceeding the threshold for NI Receive.

dsFmcSetNiXmtUpperBwThresh.name: dsFmcSetNiXmtUpperBwThresh
dsFmcSetNiXmtUpperBwThresh.description: The total traffic through the unit has exceeded the configured threshold for NI Transmit.

dsFmcClrNiXmtUpperBwThresh.name: dsFmcClrNiXmtUpperBwThresh
dsFmcClrNiXmtUpperBwThresh.description: The total traffic through the unit has crossed back under 20 percent below the configured threshold after exceeding the threshold NI Transmit.

dsFmcFpingLinkDown.name: dsFmcFpingLinkDown
dsFmcFpingLinkDown.description: A VC has transitioned to a link down since FPINGs are not being returned

dsFmcFpingLinkUp.name: dsFmcFpingLinkUp
dsFmcFpingLinkUp.description: A VC has transitioned to a link up since an FPING was just returned

dsMcNetif.name: dsMcNetif
dsMcNetif.description: The management access port(s) for Telnet and SNMP. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION mcNetNone(1) No ip interface paths are active mcNetEthernet(2) The ethernet ip interface is active mcNetPppSlip(3) The ppp/slip (control ports) ip interfaces are active mcNetSlip(4) The slip (control ports) ip interface is active mcNetDatalink(5) The data link ip interface is active mcNetES(6) The ethernet and slip (control ports) ip interfaces are active mcNetED(7) The ethernet and data link ip interfaces are active mcNetESD(8) The ethernet, slip (control ports), and data link ip interfaces are active mcNetPSD(9) The ppp/slip (control ports) and data link ip interfaces are active mcNetSD(10) The slip (control ports) and data link ip interfaces are active mcNetInband(11) The inband Frame Relay (NI and Data Port) ip interface is active

dsMcT1DLPath.name: dsMcT1DLPath
dsMcT1DLPath.description: The T1 DataLink value. This configuration is used if the NETIF has a DataLink component. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION mcDLPathFdl(1) The DataLink will use the FDL. mcDLPathTSn-64 The DataLink will use TSn. If TSn is IDLE, the data rate will be set to 64K. If TSn is assigned to a Data Port, the DataLink will use 8K of TSn. mcDLPathTSn-56 The DataLink will use TSn. If TSn is IDLE, the data rate will be set to 56K. If TSn is assigned to a Data Port, the DataLink will use 8K of TSn.

dsMcCIpAddr.name: dsMcCIpAddr
dsMcCIpAddr.description: The IP address for the unit's Control Port.

dsMcDIpAddr.name: dsMcDIpAddr
dsMcDIpAddr.description: The IP address for the unit's Data Link.

dsMcCDIpMask.name: dsMcCDIpMask
dsMcCDIpMask.description: The IP subnet mask for the unit's Control Port and Data Link.

dsMcEIpAddr.name: dsMcEIpAddr
dsMcEIpAddr.description: The IP address for the unit's Ethernet Port.

dsMcEIpMask.name: dsMcEIpMask
dsMcEIpMask.description: The IP subnet mask for the unit's Ethernet Port.

dsMcIIpAddr.name: dsMcIIpAddr
dsMcIIpAddr.description: The IP address for the unit's In-Band Interface.

dsMcIIpMask.name: dsMcIIpMask
dsMcIIpMask.description: The IP subnet mask for the unit's In-Band Interface.

dsAmcAgent.name: dsAmcAgent
dsAmcAgent.description: The operational status of the SMMP agent. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION. amcEnabled(1) The SNMP agent is enabled amcDisabled(2) The SNMP agent is disabled.

dsAmcSourceScreen.name: dsAmcSourceScreen
dsAmcSourceScreen.description: The status of the IP source address screening security. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION mcIpScreen(1) The screening security is enabled mcNoScreen(2) The screening security is disabled

dsAmcTrapTable.name: dsAmcTrapTable
dsAmcTrapTable.description: The SNMP Trap Table. This table lists the different types of traps and allows each type to be individually enabled/disabled. Currently, the types of traps are: Start Traps - Cold-Start and Warm-Start Link Traps - Link-Up and Link-Down Traps Authentication Traps - e.g. incorrect Telnet password Enterprise Traps - e.g. NI EER Trap

dsAmcTrapEntry.name: dsAmcTrapEntry
dsAmcTrapEntry.description: An entry in the SNMP Trap Table.

dsAmcTrapType.name: dsAmcTrapType
dsAmcTrapType.description: The type of trap. There is one row in dsAmcTrapTable for each type of trap. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION amcStartTraps(1) Cold-Start and Warm-Start Traps. amcLinkTraps(2) Link-Up and Link-Down Traps. amcAuthenTraps(3) Authentication Traps. Sent for: - Incorrect Telnet password - Source IP address not on IP Screen List - Incorrect SNMP Read Community String - Incorrect SNMP Write Community String amcEnterpriseTraps(4) Enterprise-Specific Traps.

dsAmcTrapStatus.name: dsAmcTrapStatus
dsAmcTrapStatus.description: Indicates whether the particular type of trap is enabled or disabled. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION amcEnabled(1) These types of traps are enabled. amcDisabled(2) These types of traps are disabled.

dsAmcScrnTable.name: dsAmcScrnTable
dsAmcScrnTable.description: The Source Address Screening Table. The entries in this table are the IP addresses which are allowed to access this unit.

dsAmcScrnEntry.name: dsAmcScrnEntry
dsAmcScrnEntry.description: An entry in the Source Address Screening Table.

dsAmcScrnIndex.name: dsAmcScrnIndex
dsAmcScrnIndex.description: The index to the Source Address Screening Table. Ten entries are possible.

dsAmcScrnIpAddr.name: dsAmcScrnIpAddr
dsAmcScrnIpAddr.description: An IP Address(es) which will be permitted to access this unit. This object is combined with dsAmcScrnIpMask to allow a single entry to permit access by an entire subnet.

dsAmcScrnIpMask.name: dsAmcScrnIpMask
dsAmcScrnIpMask.description: An IP subnet mask that indicates which portion of dsAmcScrnIpAddr must be matched to permit access. This allows a single entry to provide access by an entire IP subnet. A mask of '255.255.255.0' means that hosts on the subnet of dsAmcScrnIpAddr are permitted access. A mask of '255.255.255.255' means that only the IP address which exactly matches dsAmcScrnIpAddr is permitted access (i.e. only a single host).

dsAmcTrapDestTable.name: dsAmcTrapDestTable
dsAmcTrapDestTable.description: The SNMP Trap Destinations Table. This table lists up to 10 addresses to send SNMP traps to when alarm conditions occur.

dsAmcTrapDestEntry.name: dsAmcTrapDestEntry
dsAmcTrapDestEntry.description: An entry in the SNMP Trap Destinations Table.

dsAmcTrapDestIndex.name: dsAmcTrapDestIndex
dsAmcTrapDestIndex.description: The index to the SNMP Trap Destinations Table.

dsAmcTrapDestIpAddr.name: dsAmcTrapDestIpAddr
dsAmcTrapDestIpAddr.description: The IP address portion of a Trap Destination Entry, used when sending SNMP traps.

dsAmcTrapDestVc.name: dsAmcTrapDestVc
dsAmcTrapDestVc.description: The VC portion of a Trap Destination Entry, used when sending SNMP traps.

dsAmcTrapDestPort.name: dsAmcTrapDestPort
dsAmcTrapDestPort.description: The Port portion of a Trap Destination Entry, used when sending SNMP traps.

dsMcIPort.name: dsMcIPort
dsMcIPort.description: fill in later The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION amcNiPort(1) Communicate over NI amcDPPort(2) communicate over DP

dsNcFraming.name: dsNcFraming
dsNcFraming.description: The type of framing being used on the Network Interface. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncSF(1) SF (D4) framing ncESF(2) ESF framing ncEricsson(3) Ericsson framing

dsNcCoding.name: dsNcCoding
dsNcCoding.description: The type of line coding being used on the Network Interface. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncAmi(1) AMI line coding ncB8zs(2) B8ZS line coding.

dsNcT1403.name: dsNcT1403
dsNcT1403.description: This object enables/disables the sending of T1.403 PRM messages. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncT1403Enable(1) Enable T1.403 messages ncT1403Disable(2) Disabled T1.403 messages

dsNcYellow.name: dsNcYellow
dsNcYellow.description: This object enables/disables sending Yellow alarm out the Network Interface upon receipt of an alarm on the Network Interface. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncYelEnable(1) Enable sending Yellow alarm ncYelDisable(1) Disable sending Yellow alarm

dsNcAddr54.name: dsNcAddr54
dsNcAddr54.description: If 54016 addressing is enabled, this object determines what type of addressing the unit responds to. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncAddrCsu(1) CSU addressing mode ncAddrDsu(2) DSU addressing mode ncAddrBoth(3) Both CSU and DSU addressing modes

dsNc54016.name: dsNc54016
dsNc54016.description: This object determines whether the unit responds to 54016 addressing modes. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION nc54016Enable(1) Enabled 54016 addressing nc54016Disable(2) Disable 54016 addressing

dsNcLbo.name: dsNcLbo
dsNcLbo.description: The Network Interface Line Build Out setting. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncLbo0(1) 0.0dB line attenuation ncLbo1(2) 7.5dB line attenuation ncLbo2(3) 15.0 dB line attenuation

dsNcMF16.name: dsNcMF16
dsNcMF16.description: The E1 network interface Time Slot 16 MultiFrame alignment signal setting. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncMF16Enable(1) Enable the Time Slot 16 MultiFrame alignment signal ncMF16Disable(2) Disabled the Time Slot 16 MultiFrame alignment signal

dsNcCRC.name: dsNcCRC
dsNcCRC.description: The E1 network interface CRC generation/checking setting. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncCrcEnable(1) Enable CRC generation/checking ncCrcDisable(2) Disable CRC generation/checking

dsNcFasAlign.name: dsNcFasAlign
dsNcFasAlign.description: The E1 network interface Time Slot 0 NOT-FAS Word setting. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncFasWord(1) Use the NOT-FAS word ncNonFasWord(2) Do not use the NOT-FAS word

dsNcE1DLPath.name: dsNcE1DLPath
dsNcE1DLPath.description: The E1 network interface Sa bit usage. If Sa bits are being used for data link communications, both the near and far end units must agree on which Sa bit to use. Possible value are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncSaNone(1) No Sa bits are being used for data link communications ncSaBit4(2) Use Sa bit 4 for data link communications ncSaBit5(3) Use Sa bit 5 for data link communications ncSaBit6(4) Use Sa bit 6 for data link communications ncSaBit7(5) Use Sa bit 7 for data link communications ncSaBit8(6) Use Sa bit 8 for data link communications ncTSn Use TimeSlot n for data link communications. These are only available for E1 units with In-Band Link hardware.

dsNcKA.name: dsNcKA
dsNcKA.description: The status of sending E1 remote Frame Alarm into the NI during alarms. The Possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncFramedKeepAlive(1) Enable Framed Keep Alive ncUnFramedKeepAlive(2) Disabled Unframed Keep Alive

dsNcGenRfa.name: dsNcGenRfa
dsNcGenRfa.description: The status of sending E1 remote Frame Alarm into the NI during alarms. The Possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncGenRfaEnable(1) Enable RFA insertion ncGenRfaDisable(2) Disabled RFA insertion

dsNcPassTiRfa.name: dsNcPassTiRfa
dsNcPassTiRfa.description: The status of sending the RFA received on the network interface out the terminal interface. This function is not possible on a DSU only, it must be an add/drop. This function only works if at least one channel is assigned to the TI. The Possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION ncPassTiRfaEnable(1) Enable RFA re-generation ncPassTiRfaDisable(2) Disabled RFA re-generation

dsNcIdle.name: dsNcIdle
dsNcIdle.description: The idle code to be transmited in the idle NI and TI channels. This code is also sent in all TI channels when the TI is experiencing an OOF.

dsNcDdsType.name: dsNcDdsType
dsNcDdsType.description: The Possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION scDds56K(1) Set unit to 56K Operation scDds64K(2) Set unit to 56K Operation

dsScMonth.name: dsScMonth
dsScMonth.description: The calendar number of the current month. 1 is January.

dsScDay.name: dsScDay
dsScDay.description: The number of the current day.

dsScYear.name: dsScYear
dsScYear.description: The number of the current year. 95 is 1995.

dsScHour.name: dsScHour
dsScHour.description: The number of the current hour. 0 is 12:00am.

dsScMinutes.name: dsScMinutes
dsScMinutes.description: The number of the current minute.

dsScName.name: dsScName
dsScName.description: The Site Name of the unit.

dsScSlotAddr.name: dsScSlotAddr
dsScSlotAddr.description: The Kentrox-specific slot address. The 01 in the address 01:02:003.

dsScShelfAddr.name: dsScShelfAddr
dsScShelfAddr.description: The Kentrox-specific shelf address. The 02 in the address 01:02:003.

dsScGroupAddr.name: dsScGroupAddr
dsScGroupAddr.description: The Kentrox-specific group address. The 003 in the address 01:02:003.

dsScFrontPanel.name: dsScFrontPanel
dsScFrontPanel.description: The status of the front panel buttons. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION scFpEnable(1) Enable the front panel buttons scFpDisable(2) Disable the front panel buttons

dsScDSCompatible.name: dsScDSCompatible
dsScDSCompatible.description: The status of the datasmart compatibility function. This should be set to scDSEnabled(1) when the far end unit is a eariler model datasmart, not a datasmart. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION scDSEnable(1) Enable the datasmart compatibility function scDSDisable(2) Disable the datasmart compatibility funcation

dsScClockSource.name: dsScClockSource
dsScClockSource.description: The source of the timing clock. The various options are: VALUE DESCRIPTION scTerminalTiming(1) Use the clock coming in on the Terminal Interface scThroughTiming(2) Use Through timing NI rx to Ti tx and TI rx to NI tx scInternalTiming(3) Use the internal clock scLoopTiming(4) Use the clock from the network scDP1Timing(5) Use the clock coming in on data port 1 scDP2Timing(6) Use the clock coming in on data port 2

dsScAutologout.name: dsScAutologout
dsScAutologout.description: The time (in minutes) to wait for a keypress before logging the current user out. If this object is set to 0, autologout is disabled.

dsScZeroPerData.name: dsScZeroPerData
dsScZeroPerData.description: This object will zero all performance report counters if it is set to scZallStart(2).

dsScWyv.name: dsScWyv
dsScWyv.description: The string returned by the user interface command WYV, What's Your Version.

dsScAutoCfg.name: dsScAutoCfg
dsScAutoCfg.description: This object enables/disables the Auto-Configuration feature, which allows units in a daisy chain to be automatically configured by the Daisy Chain Controller. This feature is only available on the plug-in versions of datasmart.

dsScTftpSwdl.name: dsScTftpSwdl
dsScTftpSwdl.description: A text string used to initiate or check the status of a TFTP file transfer operation for doing a software download. To initiate a TFTP software download, set this variable to the value `tswdl:<i>,<f>`, where i represents the IP address of the host system, and the f represents the name of the file to be downloaded. Setting this variable to any other value will have no affect. Getting the value of this variable will return the status of the TFTP software download.

dsScBoot.name: dsScBoot
dsScBoot.description: This variable is used to force a system reboot: scBootIdle Does nothing. scBootActive Reboots from the executing FLASH ROM bank. scBootInactive Reboots from the non-executing FLASH ROM bank.

dsScOperMode.name: dsScOperMode
dsScOperMode.description: fill in later. scTransparentMode Unit doesn't monitor FR traffic scMonitorMode Unit monitors FR traffic

dsTcFraming.name: dsTcFraming
dsTcFraming.description: The line framing for the Terminal Interface. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION tcSF(1) SF (D4) framing tcESF(2) ESF framing tcEricsson(3) Ericsson framing

dsTcCoding.name: dsTcCoding
dsTcCoding.description: The line coding for the Terminal Interface. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION tcAmi(1) AMI line coding tcB8zs(2) B8ZS line coding

dsTcIdle.name: dsTcIdle
dsTcIdle.description: The code that is sent out the idle DS0 channels of the terminal interface.

dsTcEqual.name: dsTcEqual
dsTcEqual.description: The line equalization for the Terminal Interface. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION tcTe0(1) 0-133 feet tcTe1(2) 133-266 feet tcTe2(3) 266-399 feet tcTe3(4) 399-533 feet tcTe4(5) 533-655 feet

dsTcMF16.name: dsTcMF16
dsTcMF16.description: The E1 terminal interface Time Slot 16 MultiFrame alignment signal setting. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION tcMF16Enable(1) Enable the Time Slot 16 MultiFrame alignment signal tcMF16Disable(2) Disabled the Time Slot 16 MultiFrame alignment signal

dsTcCRC.name: dsTcCRC
dsTcCRC.description: The E1 terminal interface CRC generation/checking setting. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION tcCrcEnable(1) Enable CRC generation/checking tcCrcDisable(2) Disable CRC generation/checking

dsTcFasAlign.name: dsTcFasAlign
dsTcFasAlign.description: The E1 terminal interface Time Slot 0 NOT-FAS Word setting. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION tcFasWord(1) Use the NOT-FAS word tcNonFasWord(2) Do not use the NOT-FAS word

dsTcAis.name: dsTcAis
dsTcAis.description: This object controls the sending of Alarm Indication Signal (AIS) alarms. The possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION tcAisEnable(1) Enable sending AIS alarms tcAisDisable(2) Disable sending AIS alarms

dsTcGenRfa.name: dsTcGenRfa
dsTcGenRfa.description: The status of sending E1 remote Frame Alarm into the TI during alarms. The Possible values are: VALUE DESCRIPTION tcGenRfaEnable(1) Enable RFA insertion tcGenRfaDisable(2) Disabled RFA insertion

dsTcPassTiRfa.name: dsTcPassTiRfa
dsTcPassTiRfa.description: The status of sending the RFA received on the terminal interface out the network interface. This function is not possible on a DSU only, it must be an add/drop.
